main event: A civilian reported observing an unidentified flying object in Doylestown, Pennsylvania on November 15, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for one hour and moved in an ESE direction., The object was described as round and white in color., The witness noted that the object climbed into cloud cover before disappearing., The sky conditions were bright and clear at the time of the observation., There were no photographs or physical evidence associated with the sighting.
